  "explanation": "IBM MQ requires the proprietary `pymqi` client library and connects to a queue manager over a named SVRCONN channel. The two required fields (`channel`, `queue_manager`) are MQ-administrative identifiers that are not discoverable from the wire \u2014 every site picks its own naming. Production deployments add username/password and/or SSL with a key repository and cipher spec. None of this can be discovered by probing the listener port (1414); even discovering the existence of an MQ listener does not yield a working configuration.",
